reviewText: Started to watch this dvd but haven't finished it yet but trust its in good condition thank you

Natalie Wood (Natasha Gurdin) was an underrated actress who was beautiful, believable and funny,  These two comedies are well worth viewing. The scenes of a suicide attempt (head in an electric oven?) and Lauren Bacall and Henry Fonda doing a romantic anniversary dance (The Twist?) are subtle and silly and very funny.  Look for more apt and timely comments o  pop culture, particularly if you're over 60.
